error: unknown subcommand 'batch'
HEXA — self-hosted language toolchain

USAGE:
    hexa <SUBCOMMAND> [ARGS...]

SUBCOMMANDS:
    run <file> [args...]    Execute a .hexa script (interpreter)
    batch <f1> <f2> ...     Run N scripts sharing one CLI dispatch
                              Each result delimited by ===BATCH_RESULT===
    parse <file>            Parse-only check (no exec, no codegen)
    test <file> [opts]      Run @test fn in <file> (native runner)
                              opts: --filter NAME (substring match)
                                    --verbose (per-test stdout)
                                    --selftest-only (legacy --selftest path)
    check <file>            Verify @invariant DSL blocks (AST-based)
    convergence <subcmd>    Scan source-embedded convergence metadata (3 formats)
                              dump <file>       full snapshot (JSON)
                              dump-meta <file>  project-level meta only
                            Formats:
                              A) # @convergence-start/end  multi-line block (legacy)
                              B) # @convergence k=v k="v"  single-line comment (.md)
                              C) @convergence(k="v", ...)  hexa attribute (.hexa)
    build <file> [-o out]   Compile .hexa to native binary
    bench <file> [opts]     Benchmark a .hexa script (wall/RSS/alloc)
                              opts: --runs N (default 3)
                                    --json (JSON output, no table)
                                    --compare <other_bin> (A/B vs second binary)
    cc                      Rebuild the transpiler (hexa_cc)
    gc [--dry-run]          Prune .hexa-cache slots older than 30d
                              Env: HEXA_CACHE=0 disables AOT cache
                              fast-path (forces stage0 interpreter).
    lsp                     Start LSP server (stdin/stdout, JSON-RPC)
    status                  Show toolchain status
    version                 Print version
    init <dir> [--name N]   Scaffold <dir>/project.hexa (0% external format)
    smash|free|thinking|lens|atlas|bus|roadmap|discovery
                            Delegate to $NEXUS/shared/bin/nexus-cli
                              hexa smash --seed "..." [--depth 3]
                              hexa free --seed "..." [--dfs 3]
    url <hexa://URL>        Dispatch a hexa:// URL (macOS URL handler)
                              Schemes: hexa://run?file=PATH
                                       hexa://repl?dir=PATH
                                       hexa://install?pkg=NAME
    help                    Show this help
